-- New York's DiNapoli Says Jobless-Benefit Extension Worth $12.9 Bn to State
-- B y   J o A n n e   N o r t o n
-- 2010-12-03T16:43:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-03/new-york-s-dinapoli-says-jobless-benefit-extension-worth-12-9-bn-to-state.html
New York’s economy will be reduced by
$12.9 billion if Congress doesn’t reinstate extended
unemployment benefits New York State Comptroller Thomas P.
DiNapoli said, citing a study by his office.  DiNapoli’s analysis said about 200,000 of New York’s
jobless-benefits recipients, or 38 percent, will lose their
benefits this month if the extension isn’t renewed.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
JoAnne Norton at 
 jnorton@bloomberg.net  